    "Adebayo Ogunlesi is chairman, CEO and a cofounder of Global Infrastructure Partners, a private equity firm headquartered in New York.",
    "Founded in 2006, the firm owns infrastructure assets in the energy, transport, digital infrastructure, and water and waste management sectors.",
    "Prior to starting GIP, Ogunlesi spent 23 years in the investment banking unit of Credit Suisse and earlier was an attorney at Cravath, Swaine & Moore, a law firm in New York.",
    "Born in Nigeria, he attend Kings College Lagos, a prominent boarding school in the country.",
    "His father, Theophilus Oladipo Ogunlesi, was reportedly the first professor of medicine in Nigeria."
